{"type":null,"faqId":26410,"title":"Handling Breakdown","answer":"<p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:center\" align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333\">Handling Breakdown</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">It is not rare to encounter phone\nbreakdown, but frequent breakdown will affect user experience. Try the\nfollowing methods to prevent or handle breakdown. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:center;\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:21.0pt;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:18.75pt;text-align:\nleft;text-indent:-18.75pt;\n\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\ncolor:#333333;\"><span>1.<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Times New Roman','serif';color:#333333;\">Do\nnot run too many applications simultaneously. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Instead of exiting an application, some\nusers are used to simply returning to the home screen. However, the application\nkeeps running in the background. If too may applications are running\nsimultaneously, your phone may break down. Exit applications when you do not\nneed them, and run only one large application at a time. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Times New Roman','serif';color:#333333;\">2.\nRegularly scan for viruses.</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Your phone may be attacked by viruses. Try\nto scan for and eliminate viruses using a security application. If the problem\npersists, save important data and restore your phone to its factory settings or\nformat the microSD card. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Times New Roman','serif';color:#333333;\">3.\nCheck the microSD card.</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Remove the microSD card and check whether\nthe problem persists. If the problem is solved, the microSD card may have data\nprotection or conflict. Delete unnecessary items one by one, or format the\nmicroSD card. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">4. Do not operate your phone too quickly if\nits specifications are low. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Sending commands too quickly to the phone\nmay result in breakdown if your phone's specifications are low. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">5. Check whether the battery is properly\nconnected to peripheral components. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">If your phone has been used for a long\ntime, the battery may fail to connect to peripheral components. Restore your\nphone to its factory settings and check whether it still frequently breaks\ndown. If yes, replace the battery. </span><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\ncolor:#333333;\"><br>\n</span><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';color:#333333;\">6. Do not play large games while charging. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Your phone is prone to breakdown when its\ntemperature is high, which is its self-protection mechanism. If your phone\ngenerates excessive heat, do not play large games while charging it. </span></p>\n<br>\n</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"789","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1433163476000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":2,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Handling Breakdown","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}